<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1745,2024]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1437,153,467]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,421,1817,1844]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Whole fly as 
<figureCitation box="[583,667,1817,1843]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–101" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
. Head as 
<figureCitation box="[779,863,1817,1844]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–101" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
. Frons as 
<figureCitation box="[980,1063,1817,1843]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–101" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
, totally lacking fine microtrichia (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,1853,1879]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–101" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
). Cheek with 6 strong bristles and jowl with 3, one longer and 2 similar to those on cheek. Postpedicels, which lack SPS vesicles, and proboscis as 
<figureCitation box="[634,717,1889,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–101" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
. Proboscis from below as 
<figureCitation box="[1015,1098,1889,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–101" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
. Thorax brown, with 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these, and mesopleuron as 
<figureCitation box="[878,975,1925,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–101" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
. Scutellum with an anterior pair of small hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites brown, 2–6 with numerous hairs towards lateral margins but minute hairs along the median band; some longer hairs at rear of T5 and long bristles at rear of T6 (
<figureCitation box="[1325,1423,1997,2023]" captionStart="FIGURES 94–101" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
). Venter gray with relatively few small hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[1021,1177,153,179]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 94–101" captionStart-1="FIGURES 102–109" captionStartId-0="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionStartId-1="17.[151,264,1899,1924]" captionTargetBox-0="[219,1372,195,1903]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1435,489,1867]" captionTargetId-0="figure@16.[199,1389,181,1916]" captionTargetId-1="figure@17.[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetPageId-0="16" captionTargetPageId-1="17" captionText-0="FIGURES 94–101. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 94, whole fly; 95, head; 96, frons; 97, detail of frons; 98, postpedicels and proboscis from above; 99, the same from below; 100, side view of thorax; 101, side view from segments 5 to tip of abdomen. Scale bars 20 μm." captionText-1="FIGURES 102–109. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 102, left face of epandrium; 103, right face of hypopygium; 104, left face of hypandrium; 105, front tarsus; 106, front basitarsus; 107, hind femur; 108, hind tibia; 109, wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573392" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3573392/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 101–103</figureCitation>
. The hypandrium has a small bristle each side and unusually has a tapered process between them (
<figureCitation box="[992,1091,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 102–109" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1899,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,489,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 102–109. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 102, left face of epandrium; 103, right face of hypopygium; 104, left face of hypandrium; 105, front tarsus; 106, front basitarsus; 107, hind femur; 108, hind tibia; 109, wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573392/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
). Legs with brown femora and tibiae. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisades on segments 1–4 and 5 a little longer than 4 (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1332,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 102–109" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1899,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,489,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 102–109. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 102, left face of epandrium; 103, right face of hypopygium; 104, left face of hypandrium; 105, front tarsus; 106, front basitarsus; 107, hind femur; 108, hind tibia; 109, wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573392/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 105</figureCitation>
). The basitarsus has some rows of hairs reduced to much shorter and finer hairs (
<figureCitation box="[958,1056,261,288]" captionStart="FIGURES 102–109" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1899,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,489,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 102–109. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 102, left face of epandrium; 103, right face of hypopygium; 104, left face of hypandrium; 105, front tarsus; 106, front basitarsus; 107, hind femur; 108, hind tibia; 109, wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573392/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.84 times its length. Hairs below basal half of hind femur about as long as those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation box="[307,407,333,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 102–109" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1899,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,489,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 102–109. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 102, left face of epandrium; 103, right face of hypopygium; 104, left face of hypandrium; 105, front tarsus; 106, front basitarsus; 107, hind femur; 108, hind tibia; 109, wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573392/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia with 6 of the 8 differentiated posterodorsal hairs robust, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple (
<figureCitation box="[581,681,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 102–109" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1899,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,489,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 102–109. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 102, left face of epandrium; 103, right face of hypopygium; 104, left face of hypandrium; 105, front tarsus; 106, front basitarsus; 107, hind femur; 108, hind tibia; 109, wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573392/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
). Wings (
<figureCitation box="[790,887,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 102–109" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1899,1924]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,489,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1435,489,1873]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 102–109. Megaselia evogliensis n. sp. male. 102, left face of epandrium; 103, right face of hypopygium; 104, left face of hypandrium; 105, front tarsus; 106, front basitarsus; 107, hind femur; 108, hind tibia; 109, wing. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573392/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 109</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[904,1005,369,395]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.63" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="1.63">1.63 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.41. Costal ratios 3.50: 1.29: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[606,720,405,431]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="0.032">0.032 mm</quantity>
long. Vein 3 hair 
<quantity box="[917,1030,404,431]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="0.025">0.025 mm</quantity>
long. 2 unequal axillary bristles, the outermost being 
<quantity box="[339,439,440,467]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob brown.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573390" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3573390" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573390/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" startId="16.[151,264,1942,1967]" targetBox="[219,1372,195,1903]" targetPageId="16">
